Hi Adriene, just wanted to tell you how grateful I am for you. I'm relatively young (22) but never really had much of a relationship with my body, it was there, sometimes i liked it, sometimes I hated it, most times I looked at it and never really could register that it was mine. I was just a brain in a vehicule.
Thanks to you I can breathe and know what it feels like to hear it flow everywhere. That stretching my body isn't a chore after a workout but actually me loving it and listening to each part of it.
This knowledge and realisation will follow me for the rest of my life, I really don't know how I can repay you haha
I also noticed that some practices I couldn't quiet my mind and listen to my body, and what helped my was journaling right before starting yoga.
So for anyone struggling with mind-chatter during practice, I really do advise to take 5 to 10min and just freeflow write everything that is going on in your mind. Doesn't have to make sense, just write it down. Once it's written it's purged out of your brain and you can meet your peaceful self on the mat.
Anyway, thank you Adriene. I would love to help you the same way you helped all of us. So if someday you need some sort of help, don't hesitate to reach out. You have, I think, the most grateful subscribers :)
